(24, 'Restaurant d''Vijff Vlieghen', 'Bar/Restaurant', '4.889', '52.370', '2 sterren: Vijff Vlieghen is a beautiful restaurant located in old Amsterdam houses. The decor is authentic from the walls to the chairs. Every room has its unique feel. Depending on the size of your group you might be upstairs, downstairs, in a small room. Coat check at the door. The food is meant to be modern twist on Dutch classics. The menu is small and changes often. The pre fixe menu is expensive for only 3 courses. The presentation of each dish is complex and beautiful. Â Everything is placed carefully on the plate. From the main items (meats, fish , potatoes) to the herbs and spices. It is a pleasure for the eyes. However such great visual effects have to be followed with tasty flavors. d&#39;Vijff Vlieghen fails in this area. Most the dishes were blend, not seasoned right and lukewarm.After the appetizers, we were dreading the main dishes.We tried:Sliced Duck Breastyelp.com/biz_photos/restâ€¦Beautifully presented and cut duck breast. The slices were really thin, and the dressing drizzle was visually powerful. In the mouth it was not so flavorful, and quite blend.Smoked Salmonyelp.com/biz_photos/restâ€¦A simple dish. This dish can be bought in any breakfast/brunch place in Amsterdam. The fish did not taste better here. Nothing made this dish shine. Boring to the palate.Pheasantyelp.com/biz_photos/restâ€¦Brown and sad. That is the description of this dish. The pheasant was cooked right and the meat was tender but it had no flavors. The Â seasoning went on another dish that was not served to us.Chickenyelp.com/biz_photos/restâ€¦When we thought the colors and taste of the pheasant could not have been more wrong, we tried the chicken. The overall dish looked so dark, with a flavorless black sauce. In the dark lighting of this restaurant it felt like a middle-ages dish cooked by a middle ages chef and not modern cuisine.Creamy Dessertyelp.com/biz_photos/restâ€¦Probably the best dish of the night ( which was not difficult). A light creamy dessert.d&#39;Vijff Vlieghen is an institution. It is in guide books, and international newspapers. The quality of the presentation was on par with upscale restaurant. The flavors and tastes were below average.I do not recommend d&#39;Vijff Vlieghen.', NULL, NULL),
